aspguidp.helper

Class ValueSourceHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • aspguidp.helper.ValueSourceHelper

  • public class ValueSourceHelper
extends java.lang.Object
    Helper class which provides static methods for extracting values for a value source from a collection of atoms.

    A value source is either a predicate value source like 'node' or 'edge[0]' or a type like '#int'. A predicate value source consists of a predicate name and an optional argument index. For example, the predicate value source 'edge[0]' contains the predicate name 'edge' and the argument index '0'. Values for a predicate value source are the values of the argument respective to the argument index of atoms with the respective predicate name. If a predicate value source contains no argument index, the argument index is set to 0 per default. If the value source is a type, values for the type value source are values of the respective type.

    • Method Detail

      • getValues

        public static java.util.List<java.lang.String> getValues(java.util.Collection<Atom> sourceAtoms,
                                                         java.lang.String valueSource,
                                                         java.lang.String startsWith)
        Extract values for the given value source from the given collection of atoms. If the given starting string is not empty, the returned values are filtered, so that every returned value starts with the content of the given string

        This method is used to generate suggestions for possible values. For example: when generating suggestions for the 'from' attribute of an 'edge' entity, the 'from' attribute has the value source 'node[0]'. In this case, this method is called with all the atoms of the program, the value source 'node[0]' and the current user input. The returned list of values will contain all values from the value source 'node[0]', which start with the given user input.

        Parameters:
        sourceAtoms - collection of atoms which is used to extract values for the given value source
        valueSource - value source for which the values are extracted
        startsWith - string which must be the beginning of returned values
        Returns:
        list of values for the given value source extracted from the given atoms which begin with the given start string.
